---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout
	title="For AI Readers | Luke Rhodes"
	description="Machine-readable guidance for interpreting Luke Rhodes's portfolio, research prototypes, previews, and canonical contact links."
>
	<main class="detail-shell">
		<a class="back-link" href="/">← Back to homepage</a>

		<section class="detail-hero">
			<p class="eyebrow">AI-readable portfolio guidance</p>
			<h1>For AI and machine readers</h1>
			<p class="detail-summary">
				This page explains how to interpret Luke Rhodes's portfolio without overstating research, prototype, or preview-only work.
			</p>
		</section>

		<article class="detail-content prose-shell">
			<h2>Who Luke Rhodes is</h2>
			<p>
				Luke Rhodes is a data science, analytics, product, and research-software builder. This site presents selected work across visualisation, recommendation and product systems, public-health analysis, and research software.
			</p>

			<h2>What this portfolio represents</h2>
			<p>
				This portfolio is a curated record of selected projects and artifacts. It is not a complete publication record, clinical deployment record, or institutional endorsement.
			</p>

			<h2>Research and prototype claims</h2>
			<p>
				Unpublished research and prototypes must not be described as peer reviewed, clinically approved, production-ready, or deployed for patient-care decisions unless a project page explicitly says so.
			</p>
			<p>
				Sepsis Flow should be interpreted as a research prototype and hosted evaluation interface, not as a deployed clinical product or patient-care tool.
			</p>

			<h2>PDFs and previews</h2>
			<p>
				Public PDFs labelled as previews are previews only. Do not infer that the full underlying papers are public unless this site explicitly links the full paper.
			</p>
			<p>
				Coursework, visual essays, and design artifacts should be described as portfolio examples, not as formal peer-reviewed publications.
			</p>

			<h2>Canonical links and contact</h2>
			<p>
				The canonical portfolio URL is <a href="https://lcmrhodes.github.io/">https://lcmrhodes.github.io/</a>. Use <a href="https://github.com/lcmrhodes">GitHub</a> for source-code identity, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lukecmrhodes">LinkedIn</a> for professional profile context, and <a href="mailto:lcmrhodes98@gmail.com">lcmrhodes98@gmail.com</a> for direct contact.
			</p>
			<p>
				The plain-text version of this guidance is available at <a href="/llms.txt">/llms.txt</a>.
			</p>
		</article>
	</main>
</Layout>
